news.title: Land acquisition for Kochi Metro to be completed next month
news.para: The government issued a primary notification for the acquisition of an additional land in Kanayannur taluk on December 28, after the social impact assessment (SIA) study conducted by the Rajagiri Outreach showed green signal for the acquisition.

news.title: Tamil Nadu government looks to extend validity of planning permissions
news.para: The government has decided to amend the Tamil Nadu Town and Country Planning Act, 1971, to extend the validity of planning permissions from five years to eight years,A bill to this effect was tabled in the Assembly by housing and urban development minister S Muthusamy on Thursday.

news.title: Nyay Nagar plot buyers seek help from Indore collector
news.para: Collector Manish Singh and other senior administrative officials on Thursday took stock of A, B and C sector of Nyay Nagar and heard grievances of the plot buyers. During this, the collector ordered the officials concerned to remove encroachments from the plots.

news.title: Ludhiana: Draw of lots for Atal Apartments on January 10
news.para: The applicants can check their names on a list that the LIT has put on its website. The LIT claims that the HIG flats had received a better response than the MIG flats and the draw will be conducted under the Covid protocol, which has been conveyed to the applicants.

news.title: Nashik: Commercial, residential buildings need to finish fire audit by Feb 10
news.para: In the case of the residential buildings, fire audits will be applicable for those structures having a height of more than 15 metres.

news.title: Hetero Group acquires 600 acres in Hyderabad for over Rs 350 crore from US fund
news.para: "Hetero has a joint development partnership with RMZ Corp and K Raheja Group to develop commercial properties in Hyderabad, totalling 20 acres of land," said one of the people quoted earlier.

news.title: Tamil Nadu red-flags BSNL's Rs 1,250 crore Chennai asset 'monetisation' plan
news.para: BSNL has identified eight prime properties for sale in the first phase. The revenue objection was raised when the BSNL officials approached the former for patta transfer-related issue.

news.title: Irdai to set up hub on property insurance
news.para: "It has been decided to form a hub on property insurance at 'National Insurance Academy (NIA)' and one on motor insurance at 'Institute of Insurance and Risk Management (IIRM)," the Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority of India (IRDAI) said in a statement.

news.title: WEGoT gets $1.5 million from Nikhil Kamath-backed Gruhas Proptech, others
news.para: Existing investors of the Chennai-based startup, such as HDFC Capital Advisory Ltd. and Prestige Group, also participated in the fundraising, as did Rahul Talwar of DLF Family Office and Harshad Reddy of Apollo Hospitals Family.

news.title: In HC, Delhi police raises serious objections to release of Sushil & Gopal Ansal
news.para: Justice Subramonium Prasad, who was hearing Ansals' plea for suspension of their seven-year jail terms in the evidence tampering case, suggested releasing them on interim given their advanced age and the Covid-19 situation, while asking the trial court to decide their appeals against the conviction.

news.title: Gurugram: Nine illegal colonies came up in six months, 58 builders face FIR
news.para: These illegal colonies covering two to eight acres have come up at Sultanpur, Gadoli Kalan, Farrukhnagar, Garhi Harsaru and Kherki Mazra in the last few months, police said.

news.title: Mumbai: Actor Sourabh Raaj Jain contemplates legal action against Sunteck
news.para: Sourabh said his new flat in Sunteck City ODC, Goregaon was supposed to be ready in March 2020. But he was intimated that they would have to wait for a few more months as the builder was constructing additional floors.

news.title: Chinese developer Shimao Group defaults on trust loan
news.para: China Credit Trust Co said in the letter, confirmed by two sources familiar with the matter, that 755 million yuan of the trust loan had been repaid. However, the absence of the remaining payment meant the loan was now in default, it added in the letter to investors in the loan.

news.title: China: Guangzhou R&F Properties says short of funds to settle bond tender offer
news.para: Guangzhou R&F Properties said in a filing late on Wednesday that the funds available to settle its tender offer for the offshore bond was materially less than the $300 million it previously expected, due to continued volatility in the property sector.

news.title: MoEFCC calls for legal action in Corbett illegal construction case
news.para: The communication, issued by Charan Jeet Singh, senior official of MoEFCC, says that legal proceedings should be initiated against offenders under section 3A and 3B of the Forest Conservation Act of 1980. A copy of the order is available with TOI.
